title: Brazil ejects Bolsonaro and brings back the former leftist leader Lula.
description: Brazilians voted out far-right President Jair Bolsonaro after a single term and replaced him with the former President Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva.
dc:creator: Jack Nicas

media:content.media:credit: Victor Moriyama for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva, the leftist candidate who was elected president, on the way to vote in São Bernardo do Campo, Brazil, on Sunday.
